Those attending a food bank have to make do with getting rides from friends, relatives and acquaintances. Although over 300 families are being fed through this initiative, the project has gone on hold since it is too dangerous to navigate the streets of Freetown.

Despite this setback, the number of people in need continues to increase. To support future efforts, they are in the process of building a school for 250 students and providing a restaurant for 500 people every day. Please donate to this project, and help rebuild the lives of thousands of women and children in Freetown, Sierra Leone.
